    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "Just curious, why do you use `testFail`? IMO this is an antipattern, mainly supported for backwards compatibility with dapptools which did not have `vm.expectRevert`. My suggestion would be to never use `testFail`, since it will cause the test to pass on any failure, not just a specific revert reason. Per the WIP best practices (https://github.com/foundry-rs/book/pull/686), you can use a naming convention like `test_RevertIf_Description` to make it easier to identify and filter on revert tests",
