    "body": "In this particular case I considered it, but I was testing that a function reverted if the contract wasn't initialized. Since the initialization set some addresses, it meant that the function would fail anyway by making a call to address 0 and so an explicit `require` is not needed.\r\n\r\nThe revert in this case has no message, so I could use `vm.expectRevert(\"\")`. I guess it is better than `testFail` because at least the test won't pass if failing for something that has a message. I will make this change!\r\n\r\nCould be a good addition to the best practices also!",
